2,'2014-11-25 15:47:04','2014-11-25 17:47:04','<!--:pt--><a href=\"http://www.bbc.co.uk/portuguese/noticias/2014/10/141027_eleicoes2014_mobilizacao_politica_pai\">http://www.bbc.co.uk/portuguese/noticias/2014/10/141027_eleicoes2014_mobilizacao_politica_pai</a><!--:-->','Como não deixar o debate político morrer? | BBC','','publish','closed','closed','','como-nao-deixar-o-debate-politico-morrer-bbc','','','2014-11-25 15:47:04','2014-11-25 17:47:04','',0,'http://www.itsrio.org/?p=1105',0,'comunicados_ctp','',0),(1131,1,'2015-01-16 14:02:11','2015-01-16 16:02:11','<!--:pt-->O ITS publicou dois case studies, um sobre o Marco Civil da Internet, e outro sobre o CT-Spam do CGI.br na publicação coordenada pelo NoC e o Berkman Center, da Universidade de Harvard. Material em Inglês, mas que vale muito a pena ler. Abaixo mais informações sobre o material.\n\n<a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=0ByRvOoAY_qdTVlFZdVRiUjVmR3c&amp;authuser=0\">Donwload</a>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Multistakeholder as Governance Groups: New Study by Global Network of Internet and Society Centers, January 2015</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"> The <a href=\"http://networkofcenters.net/\">Global Network of Internet and Society Research Centers (NoC)</a> and the <a href=\"http://cyber.law.harvard.edu/\">Berkman Center for Internet &amp; Society</a> at Harvard University are pleased to announce the release of a <a href=\"http://ssrn.com/abstract=2549270\">new report</a> on Multistakeholder Governance Groups, which informs the debate about Internet governance models and mechanisms.</p>\n<span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">The report is the result of a globally-coordinated academic research effort among NoC participants and consists of twelve geographically and topically diverse </span><a style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\" href=\"https://publixphere.net/i/noc/page/Internet_Governance_Research_Project_Case_Studies\">case studies</a><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\"> of governance structures, and a </span><a style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\" href=\"https://publixphere.net/i/noc/page/Internet_Governance_Research_Project_Synthesis\">synthesis paper</a><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\"> that summarizes key findings across these cases. The research examines multistakeholder governance groups with the goal of informing the future evolution of the Internet governance ecosystem. Building upon the NETmundial </span><a style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\" href=\"http://netmundial.br/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/NETmundial-Multistakeholder-Document.pdf\">Principles and Roadmap</a><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">, it contributes to current policy debates at the international level, including the Internet Governance Forum, the NETmundial Initiative, and the World Economic Forum.</span>\n\n<span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">\"We are at crossroads when it comes to the global governance of the Internet, where we must not only respond to complex technical challenges, but also deal with a broad range of policy issues ranging from cybersecurity to net neutrality and human rights,\" said Berkman Center Executive Director and Harvard Law School Professor of Practice Urs Gasser, who led the international effort. \"This collaborative research wants to strengthen the evidence-base as we search for future governance models that preserve the generativity and openness of the Internet, while also addressing pressing challenges and problems.\"</span>\n\n<span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">At a point where the future of Internet governance is being re-envisioned, the report deepens our understanding of the formation, operation, and critical success factors of governance groups. The study concludes that:</span>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">“there is no single best-fit model for multistakeholder governance groups that can be applied in all instances. Rather, it reveals a range of approaches, mechanisms, and tools available for both the formation and operation of such groups. The analysis demonstrates that the success of governance groups depends to a large degree on the careful selection, deployment, and management of suitable instruments from this ‘toolbox’. As governance groups pass through different phases of operation, conveners and facilitators must remain alert to changes in circumstances that necessitate adjustments to the approaches, mechanisms, and tools that they deploy in order to address evolving challenges from inside and from outside. The case study series provides insights into how those instruments can be deployed and adjusted over time within such groups, and highlights how their interactions with important contextual factors may be successfully managed within given resource restraints.”</p>\n<span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">Other key observations from the study, as further described in the synthesis paper, include:</span>\n<ul>\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Inclusiveness (including mechanisms for participation) and transparency are critical factors to be managed and adjusted throughout the lifecycle of governance groups.</p>\n</li>\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">How governance groups define accountability and legitimacy is highly reflective of and dependent on contextual factors.</p>\n</li>\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Different governance groups have different measures of success and effectiveness that are tied to their unique contexts and to factors that change over time.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">The report is the first study by the recently launched Global Network of Internet and Society Centers, which brings together over 30 academic institutions from around the globe. As a milestone, it demonstrates that a global network of academic research centers can create a shared repository of timely and relevant research, which includes peer-reviewed methodologies and adherence to academic standards, open data, and expertise on diverse issues related to global policy debates.  More broadly, the Network of Centers seeks to contribute to a more generalized vision and longer-term strategy for academia regarding its roles in research, facilitation and convening, and education in and communication about the Internet age.</span>\n\nThe full text of these contributions, the other <a href=\"https://publixphere.net/i/noc/page/Internet_Governance_Research_Project_Case_Studies\">case studies</a> by our international partners, and the <a href=\"https://publixphere.net/i/noc/page/Internet_Governance_Research_Project_Synthesis\">synthesis paper</a> are available on the Publixphere website, where the authors welcome comments and feedback.  The series and individual papers are also available for download from <a href=\"http://ssrn.com/abstract=2549270\">SSRN</a>.<!--:--><!--:en-->ITS published two case studies in this excellent publication coordinated by the Berkman Center and the Network of Centers (NoC). More information about it below.\n\n<a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=0ByRvOoAY_qdTVlFZdVRiUjVmR3c&amp;authuser=0\">Donwload</a>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Multistakeholder as Governance Groups: New Study by Global Network of Internet and Society Centers, January 2015</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"> The <a href=\"http://networkofcenters.net/\">Global Network of Internet and Society Research Centers (NoC)</a> and the <a href=\"http://cyber.law.harvard.edu/\">Berkman Center for Internet &amp; Society</a> at Harvard University are pleased to announce the release of a <a href=\"http://ssrn.com/abstract=2549270\">new report</a> on Multistakeholder Governance Groups, which informs the debate about Internet governance models and mechanisms.</p>\nThe report is the result of a globally-coordinated academic research effort among NoC participants and consists of twelve geographically and topically diverse <a href=\"https://publixphere.net/i/noc/page/Internet_Governance_Research_Project_Case_Studies\">case studies</a> of governance structures, and a <a href=\"https://publixphere.net/i/noc/page/Internet_Governance_Research_Project_Synthesis\">synthesis paper</a> that summarizes key findings across these cases. The research examines multistakeholder governance groups with the goal of informing the future evolution of the Internet governance ecosystem. Building upon the NETmundial <a href=\"http://netmundial.br/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/NETmundial-Multistakeholder-Document.pdf\">Principles and Roadmap</a>, it contributes to current policy debates at the international level, including the Internet Governance Forum, the NETmundial Initiative, and the World Economic Forum.\n\n\"We are at crossroads when it comes to the global governance of the Internet, where we must not only respond to complex technical challenges, but also deal with a broad range of policy issues ranging from cybersecurity to net neutrality and human rights,\" said Berkman Center Executive Director and Harvard Law School Professor of Practice Urs Gasser, who led the international effort. \"This collaborative research wants to strengthen the evidence-base as we search for future governance models that preserve the generativity and openness of the Internet, while also addressing pressing challenges and problems.\"\n\nAt a point where the future of Internet governance is being re-envisioned, the report deepens our understanding of the formation, operation, and critical success factors of governance groups. The study concludes that:\n<p dir=\"ltr\">“there is no single best-fit model for multistakeholder governance groups that can be applied in all instances. Rather, it reveals a range of approaches, mechanisms, and tools available for both the formation and operation of such groups. The analysis demonstrates that the success of governance groups depends to a large degree on the careful selection, deployment, and management of suitable instruments from this ‘toolbox’. As governance groups pass through different phases of operation, conveners and facilitators must remain alert to changes in circumstances that necessitate adjustments to the approaches, mechanisms, and tools that they deploy in order to address evolving challenges from inside and from outside. The case study series provides insights into how those instruments can be deployed and adjusted over time within such groups, and highlights how their interactions with important contextual factors may be successfully managed within given resource restraints.”</p>\nOther key observations from the study, as further described in the synthesis paper, include:\n<ul>\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Inclusiveness (including mechanisms for participation) and transparency are critical factors to be managed and adjusted throughout the lifecycle of governance groups.</p>\n</li>\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">How governance groups define accountability and legitimacy is highly reflective of and dependent on contextual factors.</p>\n</li>\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Different governance groups have different measures of success and effectiveness that are tied to their unique contexts and to factors that change over time.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\nThe report is the first study by the recently launched Global Network of Internet and Society Centers, which brings together over 30 academic institutions from around the globe. As a milestone, it demonstrates that a global network of academic research centers can create a shared repository of timely and relevant research, which includes peer-reviewed methodologies and adherence to academic standards, open data, and expertise on diverse issues related to global policy debates.  More broadly, the Network of Centers seeks to contribute to a more generalized vision and longer-term strategy for academia regarding its roles in research, facilitation and convening, and education in and communication about the Internet age.\n<p dir=\"ltr\"></p>\nThe full text of these contributions, the other <a href=\"https://publixphere.net/i/noc/page/Internet_Governance_Research_Project_Case_Studies\">case studies</a> by our international partners, and the <a href=\"https://publixphere.net/i/noc/page/Internet_Governance_Research_Project_Synthesis\">synthesis paper</a> are available on the Publixphere website, where the authors welcome comments and feedback.  The series and individual papers are also available for download from <a href=\"http://ssrn.com/abstract=2549270\">SSRN</a>.<!--:-->','Multistakeholder as Governance Groups','','trash','closed','closed','','multistakeholder-as-governance-groups__trashed','','','2015-01-16 14:02:11','2015-01-16 16:02:11','',0,'http://www.itsrio.org/?p=1131',0,'post','',0),(1228,1,'2014-12-26 16:21:45','2014-12-26 18:21:45','<!--:pt-->Tivemos mais de 140 inscritos no CopyrightX Brasil 2015 para 30 vagas, muitas inscrições de grande qualidade.\n\nParabéns a todos os aprovados!\nLISTA DE APROVADOS:\nAmanda Dudenhoeffer\nAndréia Cristina dos Santos\nAnna Cintia\nBeatriz Machado\nBianca Amaro\nBruna Castanheira\nCarolina Loureiro\nCarolina Poleze\nCarolina Veiga\nEdubiel Arturo Alpizar Sosa\nFernando Henrique Schuenck\nFilipe Medon\nGuilherme Bonfim\nHelena Lettieri\nLeandro Monteiro\nLeonardo Moura\nLeonardo De Marchi\nLívia Helayel\nLucas França\nLuiza Tangari\nManola Lovato\nMarcelle Antunes\nMiguel Patrício\nOrlando Netto\nRafael Rodrigues\nRenan Oliveira\nRodrigo Bastos\nRosâne Menta\nSabrina Fensterseifer\nVanessa Motta<!--:-->','Resultado CopyrightX 2015','','trash','closed','closed','','resultado-copyrightx-2015','','','2014-12-26 16:21:45','2014-12-26 18:21:45','',0,'http://www.itsrio.org/?p=1228',0,'post','',0),(1230,1,'2014-11-26 16:22:34','2014-11-26 18:22:34','<!--:pt-->CopyrightX 2015 no Brasil - Curso de Direitos Autorais, com certificado de Harvard, ministrado pela Internet. \n\nO CopyrightX é um curso grátis, oferecido online, com duração de 12 semanas: de 26 de Janeiro a 27 de Abril de 2015, fruto da parceria de Harvard com o ITS e a UERJ e ministrado pelo professor William Fisher da Harvard Law School.  \n\nO curso será dado por meio de duas aulas pela Internet todas as semanas. Uma das aulas semanais será dada pelo professor William Fisher da Faculdade de Direito de Harvard, e a outra ao vivo pelo time de professores da faculdade de Direito da UERJ e do ITS, que inclui os professores Ronaldo Lemos, Sérgio Branco e Carlos Affonso Pereira, conhecidos juristas na área de propriedade intelectual.\n\nOs alunos terão a oportunidade de realizar um exame final valendo certificado assinado pela Harvard Law School aos que forem aprovados.\n\nInscrições abertas para qualquer pessoa acima de 16 anos, com fluência comprovada em inglês e interesse pelas temáticas de direito autoral. Não é necessário ser advogado, qualquer área do conhecimento é bem-vinda.\n\nSerão oferecidas apenas 30 vagas nessa edição do curso, selecionadas por meio do comitê de seleção.\n\nPara se inscrever, além de preencher o formulário abaixo, é necessário enviar o currículo (em português ou inglês) e uma redação de 1 (uma) página, obrigatoriamente em inglês, para copyrightx@itsrio.org explicando seu interesse no campo dos direitos autorais. O material deve ser enviado entre os dias 3 de Novembro e 3 de Dezembro. \n\nEm caso de dúvidas, informe-nos também pelo copyrightx@itsrio.org\n\nO resultado será anunciado no dia 16 de Dezembro as aulas terão início no dia 26 de Janeiro. Boa sorte!<!--:-->','Chamada para o curso CopyrightX 2015','','trash','closed','closed','','chamada-para-o-curso-copyrightx','','','2014-11-26 16:22:34','2014-11-26 18:22:34','',0,'http://www.itsrio.org/?p=1230',0,'post','',0),(1237,1,'2014-01-28 18:16:56','2014-01-28 20:16:56','<!--:pt--><strong>Program overview\n</strong>\nThe Institute of Technology and Society (ITS) invites researchers, graduate and undergraduate students, as well as professionals working with technology policy to apply to its Global Policy Fellowship Program and spend three weeks in Brazil at ITS.\n\nOur Global Fellows will have the unique opportunity to work with the team who conceived and developed the landmark “Marco Civil” legislation, a bill protecting fundamental rights, including privacy, net neutrality and freedom of expression, approved as law in Brazil in April 2014.\n\nThe ITS Fellowship Program will offer the opportunity for those interested in internet and technology policy to deepen their knowledge about the Brazilian technology context. We prepared an intensive 3-week program for our fellows, which include visits to the biggest technology companies operating in Brazil, the Brazilian Internet Steering Committee (CGI.br) and visits to São Paulo and Brasília, including representatives from the Ministry of Justice, Ministry of Culture and Congressmen who are advocating for policies related to internet and technology.\n\nFellows will also be expected to present at least one public seminar, organized in partnership with ITS. Suggested topics can include: broadband and access policy, content regulation, copyright and creativity, consumer privacy, open government, government surveillance, data security, data innovation, freedom of expression, democracy and technology and human rights. Fellows will also have the chance to participate in the preparations of one international seminar on the topic of “democracy and technology” that ITS is organizing.\n\n<strong>Who should apply?\n</strong>\nWe are looking for students, researchers, and professionals who are following the debates in the public policy field, and who want to spend part of their summer/winter in Brazil, learning about Internet policy. Students, researchers and professionals from all backgrounds are encouraged to apply. For the selection processes, please send us:\n\n• Your complete academic and professional resume, including your Linkedin profile and other online references you want us to consider;\n• A 1-page personal statement about your motivations to work in Brazil;\n• A brief work description of your experience with technology policy;\n• Proposal for a public presentation of your work;\n• Skills in Portuguese are not required\n\nAll documents must be sent in one single e-mail message to itsrio@itsrio.org, with the subject “Global Fellows Application”\n\n<strong>Our Fellowship Package includes:</strong>\n\n- Intensive 3-week program for the fellows\n- Air tickets to São Paulo and Brasília\n- Accommodation in São Paulo and Brasília during our visits\n- Shared office space at our headquarters for three weeks\n- A visit to a “samba” music club will also be organized, but is not mandatory\n\n<strong>Our Fellowship Package does not include:</strong>\n\n- International Travelling to and from Brazil;\n- Accommodation for the three weeks in Rio de Janeiro, where our program takes place.\n\nOur team will provide tips and information about how to find accommodation in the city during that time.\n\n<strong>Relevant Dates:</strong>\n\nApplications deadline: June 24th, 2014\nAnnouncement of fellows by e-mail: June 30th 2014\nFellowship Program will start July 21st, and will finish in August 8th, 2014\n\n<a href=\"https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/ITS-Gobal-Fellowship-Program.pdf\">Download</a><!--:--><!--:en--><strong>Program overview\n</strong>\nThe Institute of Technology and Society (ITS) invites researchers, graduate and undergraduate students, as well as professionals working with technology policy to apply to its Global Policy Fellowship Program and spend three weeks in Brazil at ITS.\n\nOur Global Fellows will have the unique opportunity to work with the team who conceived and developed the landmark “Marco Civil” legislation, a bill protecting fundamental rights, including privacy, net neutrality and freedom of expression, approved as law in Brazil in April 2014.\n\nThe ITS Fellowship Program will offer the opportunity for those interested in internet and technology policy to deepen their knowledge about the Brazilian technology context. We prepared an intensive 3-week program for our fellows, which include visits to the biggest technology companies operating in Brazil, the Brazilian Internet Steering Committee (CGI.br) and visits to São Paulo and Brasília, including representatives from the Ministry of Justice, Ministry of Culture and Congressmen who are advocating for policies related to internet and technology.\n\nFellows will also be expected to present at least one public seminar, organized in partnership with ITS. Suggested topics can include: broadband and access policy, content regulation, copyright and creativity, consumer privacy, open government, government surveillance, data security, data innovation, freedom of expression, democracy and technology and human rights. Fellows will also have the chance to participate in the preparations of one international seminar on the topic of “democracy and technology” that ITS is organizing.\n\n<strong>Who should apply?\n</strong>\nWe are looking for students, researchers, and professionals who are following the debates in the public policy field, and who want to spend part of their summer/winter in Brazil, learning about Internet policy. Students, researchers and professionals from all backgrounds are encouraged to apply. For the selection processes, please send us:\n\n• Your complete academic and professional resume, including your Linkedin profile and other online references you want us to consider;\n• A 1-page personal statement about your motivations to work in Brazil;\n• A brief work description of your experience with technology policy;\n• Proposal for a public presentation of your work;\n• Skills in Portuguese are not required\n\nAll documents must be sent in one single e-mail message to itsrio@itsrio.org, with the subject “Global Fellows Application”\n\n<strong>Our Fellowship Package includes:</strong>\n\n- Intensive 3-week program for the fellows\n- Air tickets to São Paulo and Brasília\n- Accommodation in São Paulo and Brasília during our visits\n- Shared office space at our headquarters for three weeks\n- A visit to a “samba” music club will also be organized, but is not mandatory\n\n<strong>Our Fellowship Package does not include:</strong>\n\n- International Travelling to and from Brazil;\n- Accommodation for the three weeks in Rio de Janeiro, where our program takes place.\n\nOur team will provide tips and information about how to find accommodation in the city during that time.\n\n<strong>Relevant Dates:</strong>\n\nApplications deadline: June 24th, 2014\nAnnouncement of fellows by e-mail: June 30th 2014\nFellowship Program will start July 21st, and will finish in August 8th, 2014\n\n<a href=\"https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/ITS-Gobal-Fellowship-Program.pdf\">Download</a><!--:-->','Call for Fellows ITS 2014!','','trash','closed','closed','','call-for-fellows-its','','','2014-01-28 18:16:56','2014-01-28 20:16:56','',0,'http://www.itsrio.org/?p=1237',0,'post','',0),(1245,1,'2015-02-03 15:13:06','2015-02-03 17:13:06','<!--:pt-->Não há nenhuma vaga aberta neste momento.<!--:--><!--:en--><em>Open positions:</em>\n\n<strong>Project Coordinator - Innovation</strong>\nMore information <a href=\"http://itsrio.org/2016/08/03/vaga-coordenacao-da-area-repensando-inovacao/\">here</a>.<!--:-->','Jobs','','publish','closed','closed','','jobs','','','2015-02-03 15:13:06','2015-02-03 17:13:06','',0,'http://www.itsrio.org/?page_id=1245',0,'page','',0),(1259,1,'2015-02-04 21:06:06','2015-02-04 23:06:06','<!--:pt--><strong>Program overview:</strong>\n\nThe Institute of Technology and Society (ITSrio.org) invites researchers, graduate students as well as professionals working with technology policy, to apply to its Global Policy Fellowship Program and spend four weeks* in Brazil at ITS. Last year, we welcomed six fellows from all over the world, who contributed immensely for the success of the Fellowship Program. (See the list of our 2014 fellows <a href=\"http://www.itsrio.org/sobre-o-its/fellows/\">here</a>, and what they have to say about their experiences <a href=\"http://www.itsrio.org/2015/02/04/its-fellows-2014-and-what-they-said-about-their-experience/\">here</a>).\n\nOur Global Fellows will have the opportunity to work with the team who created and developed the landmark “Marco Civil” legislation, a bill protecting fundamental rights, including privacy, net neutrality and freedom of expression, approved as law in Brazil in April 2014. ITS will offer the opportunity to work with research in the five broad areas, namely:\n<ul>\n	<li>Law, democracy and technology (dealing with topics such civic engagement, online participation, and others);</li>\n	<li>Access to technology, justice and human rights (dealing with topics such as connectivity, accesibility, digital divide and others)</li>\n	<li>Internet regulation and Internet governance;</li>\n	<li>Privacy and data protection (dealing with topics such as big data, anti-survailance, data protection and mass surveilance);</li>\n	<li>Rethinking culture, media and education (working with topics such as intelectual property, digital entrepreneurship, art &amp; technology, online teaching, and others).</li>\n</ul>\nThe ITS Fellowship Program will offer the opportunity for those interested in internet and technology policy to deepen their knowledge about the Brazilian technology context. We have prepared an intensive 4-week* program for our fellows, which include visits to the biggest technology national and international companies operating in Brazil, the Brazilian Internet Steering Committee (CGI.br) and visits to São Paulo and Brasília, including meetings with representatives of the Ministry of Justice, Ministry of Culture, and Congress members who are advocating for policies related to internet and technology.\n\nDuring their stay, selected fellows will be expected to:\n<ul>\n	<li>Present at least one public seminar, organized in partnership with ITS. Suggested topics can include: broadband and access policy, content regulation, copyright and creativity, consumer privacy, open government, government surveillance, data security, data innovation, freedom of expression, democracy and technology and human rights.</li>\n	<li>To publish at least one article or webpost about their experience as a fellow in Brazil.</li>\n	<li>To collaborate with the ITS team and its projects.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong> Who should apply?</strong>\n\nWe are looking for students, researchers, and professionals who are following the debates in the public policy field, and who want to spend part of their summer/winter in Brazil, learning about Internet policy. People from all backgrounds are encouraged to apply. For the selection processes, please send us:\n<ul>\n	<li>Your complete academic and professional resume, including your LinkedIn profile and other online references you want us to consider;</li>\n	<li>A 1-page personal statement about your motivations to work in Brazil;</li>\n	<li>A brief work description of your experience with technology policy;</li>\n	<li>Proposal for a public presentation of your work;</li>\n	<li>Indication of one of the five main areas ITS which you would like to work on;</li>\n	<li>One project or idea you would be interested in developing while at ITS.</li>\n</ul>\nPortuguese skills are not required (but English is mandatory).\nAll documents must be sent in one single e-mail message to itsrio@itsrio.org, with the subject “Global Fellows Application :: YOUR NAME”.\n\n<strong>Our Fellowship Package includes:</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>Intensive 4-week* program for the fellows;</li>\n	<li>Air tickets to São Paulo and Brasília;</li>\n	<li>Accommodation in São Paulo and Brasília during the days of our visit;</li>\n	<li>Shared office space at our headquarters for four weeks*;</li>\n	<li>A visit to a “samba” music club will also be organized, but is not mandatory;</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Our Fellowship Package does not include:</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>International Traveling to and from Brazil;</li>\n	<li>Accommodation for the four weeks* in Rio de Janeiro, where our program takes place;</li>\n	<li>Other costs related to your stay in Brazil other than those mentioned above.</li>\n	<li>Necessary visa to entry the country.</li>\n</ul>\nOur team will provide tips and information about how to find accommodation in the city during that time.\n\n<strong>Relevant Dates:</strong>\n\nApplications deadline: March 20th, 2015;\nAnnouncement of fellows by e-mail: March 31st, 2015;\nFellowship Program will start: June 29th, and will finish in July 27th, 2015*;\n\n<em>* Fellows are expected to stay in Rio from 29/June/2015 to 27/Jul/2015. After this date, fellows can coordinate with ITS the possibility of staying for a longer term if they wish. Visa and costs for additional stays are to be provided by the fellows.</em><!--:--><!--:en--><strong>Program overview:</strong>\n\nThe Institute of Technology and Society (ITSrio.org) invites researchers, graduate students as well as professionals working with technology policy, to apply to its Global Policy Fellowship Program and spend four weeks* in Brazil at ITS. Last year, we welcomed six fellows from all over the world, who contributed immensely for the success of the Fellowship Program. (See the list of our 2014 fellows <a href=\"http://www.itsrio.org/sobre-o-its/fellows/\">here</a>, and what they have to say about their experiences <a href=\"http://www.itsrio.org/2015/02/04/its-fellows-2014-and-what-they-said-about-their-experience/\">here</a>).\n\nOur Global Fellows will have the opportunity to work with the team who created and developed the landmark “Marco Civil” legislation, a bill protecting fundamental rights, including privacy, net neutrality and freedom of expression, approved as law in Brazil in April 2014. ITS will offer the opportunity to work with research in the five broad areas, namely:\n<ul>\n	<li>Law, democracy and technology (dealing with topics such civic engagement, online participation, and others);</li>\n	<li>Access to technology, justice and human rights (dealing with topics such as connectivity, accesibility, digital divide and others)</li>\n	<li>Internet regulation and Internet governance;</li>\n	<li>Privacy and data protection (dealing with topics such as big data, anti-survailance, data protection and mass surveilance);</li>\n	<li>Rethinking culture, media and education (working with topics such as intelectual property, digital entrepreneurship, art &amp; technology, online teaching, and others).</li>\n</ul>\nThe ITS Fellowship Program will offer the opportunity for those interested in internet and technology policy to deepen their knowledge about the Brazilian technology context. We have prepared an intensive 4-week* program for our fellows, which include visits to the biggest technology national and international companies operating in Brazil, the Brazilian Internet Steering Committee (CGI.br) and visits to São Paulo and Brasília, including meetings with representatives of the Ministry of Justice, Ministry of Culture, and Congress members who are advocating for policies related to internet and technology.\n\nDuring their stay, selected fellows will be expected to:\n<ul>\n	<li>Present at least one public seminar, organized in partnership with ITS. Suggested topics can include: broadband and access policy, content regulation, copyright and creativity, consumer privacy, open government, government surveillance, data security, data innovation, freedom of expression, democracy and technology and human rights.</li>\n	<li>To publish at least one article or webpost about their experience as a fellow in Brazil.</li>\n	<li>To collaborate with the ITS team and its projects.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Who should apply?</strong>\n\nWe are looking for students, researchers, and professionals who are following the debates in the public policy field, and who want to spend part of their summer/winter in Brazil, learning about Internet policy. People from all backgrounds are encouraged to apply. For the selection processes, please send us:\n<ul>\n	<li>Your complete academic and professional resume, including your LinkedIn profile and other online references you want us to consider;</li>\n	<li>A 1-page personal statement about your motivations to work in Brazil;</li>\n	<li>A brief work description of your experience with technology policy;</li>\n	<li>Proposal for a public presentation of your work;</li>\n	<li>Indication of one of the five main areas ITS which you would like to work on;</li>\n	<li>One project or idea you would be interested in developing while at ITS.</li>\n</ul>\nPortuguese skills are not required (but English is mandatory).\nAll documents must be sent in one single e-mail message to itsrio@itsrio.org, with the subject “Global Fellows Application :: YOUR NAME”.\n\n<strong>Our Fellowship Package includes:</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>Intensive 4-week* program for the fellows;</li>\n	<li>Air tickets to São Paulo and Brasília;</li>\n	<li>Accommodation in São Paulo and Brasília during the days of our visit;</li>\n	<li>Shared office space at our headquarters for four weeks*;</li>\n	<li>A visit to a “samba” music club will also be organized, but is not mandatory;</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Our Fellowship Package does not include:</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>International Traveling to and from Brazil;</li>\n	<li>Accommodation for the four weeks* in Rio de Janeiro, where our program takes place;</li>\n	<li>Other costs related to your stay in Brazil other than those mentioned above.</li>\n	<li>Necessary visa to entry the country.</li>\n</ul>\nOur team will provide tips and information about how to find accommodation in the city during that time.\n\n<strong>Relevant Dates:</strong>\n\nApplications deadline: March 20th, 2015;\nAnnouncement of fellows by e-mail: March 31st, 2015;\nFellowship Program will start: June 29th, and will finish in July 27th, 2015*;\n\n<em>* Fellows are expected to stay in Rio from 29/June/2015 to 27/Jul/2015. After this date, fellows can coordinate with ITS the possibility of staying for a longer term if they wish. Visa and costs for additional stays are to be provided by the fellows.</em><!--:-->','ITS Global Policy Fellowship Program - 2015','','trash','closed','closed','','its-global-policy-fellowship-program-2015','','','2015-02-04 21:06:06','2015-02-04 23:06:06','',0,'http://www.itsrio.org/?p=1259',0,'post','',0),(1260,1,'2015-02-04 21:05:05','2015-02-04 23:05:05','<!--:pt--><p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Amar Ashar</strong></p>\nThe ITS fellowship 2014 was a terrific opportunity for me to gain more insight into the Internet policy landscape in Brazil, and the significant contributions ITS has and continues to make to research, advocacy work, and education in the country. As a fellow, it was a privilege to have very open and off-the-record conversations with policymakers, regulators, company representatives, telecom agencies, and beyond ranging on issues from net neutrality to culture and intellectual property. The fellowship also served as a forum to present on the projects that the fellows were working on, and I learned a lot about their fields, and appreciated the opportunity for feedback on my work and to offer comments on theirs. I also enjoyed learning about the research and other projects ITS was undertaking, helping to consult on and guide the direction of those projects based on my own experience and knowledge.\n\nGiven the chance, I would absolutely apply for the fellowship again. The things I found the most useful during my time in Brazil were: (1) the field trips and meetings to Brasilia and San Paulo to learn more from the stakeholders involved in Marco Civil; (2) the briefings that Ronaldo, Carlos, Fabro, and others at ITS offered with respect to the most pressing Internet policy and legal issues in the country today (and the ones they are working on), and (3) the time and space built into the program to pursue our own independent and projects and work, with the opportunity to connect it with ITS\' work and its broader network.\n\n<strong>Primavera de Filippi</strong>\n\nIt was really great to meet all the people from ITS + the other fellows. It was great to learn about the projects that the ITS is currently working on and the trips to Brasília and São Paulo were really useful to learn more about the Brazilian system. Also, the meetings with key stakeholders and regulators were also extremely useful to better understand the process of policy making in Brazil. And… very nice atmosphere, the ITS is a wonderful place to work (I miss the sunny office) and lastly the opportunity to present our research at the Varanda was also great\n\n<strong>Amalia Deloney</strong>\n\nIn short: great to meet everyone, office was accessible, visits were great (especially the Regulatory ones) and trips to Brazilia and São Paulo provided a lot of context.\n\n<strong>Kate Krontiris</strong>\n\nI loved spending so much time with young people who are really changing their reality (ahem - I mean ITS staff).  You guys were inspiring. I really appreciated the unstructured time and freedom in Rio, when we weren\'t making site visits.  Perhaps you can be more explicit that that will happen, but I loved that it allowed us to take our own trips and plan around our own interests. I liked that my fellow peers had such different expertise sets and interests than I.  I learned a lot from them.\n\nI loved spending so much time with young people who are really changing their reality (ahem - I mean ITS staff).  You guys were inspiring. I really appreciated the unstructured time and freedom in Rio, when we weren\'t making site visits.  Perhaps you can be more explicit that that will happen, but I loved that it allowed us to take our own trips and plan around our own interests. I liked that my fellow peers had such different expertise sets and interests than I.  I learned a lot from them.\n\n<strong>Allison Burtch</strong>\n\nHave you ever wondered how the global telecommunications infrastructure system is connected? What rights do people have when social media is the only way they access the internet? How is it possible to crowd-source legislation? Rio de Janeiro is a fascinating place, and an epicenter for an in-depth look at development, gentrification, and digital access. The ITS staff is a brilliant group of writers, lawyers, policy makers and technologists. I would highly recommend applying to this residency, and be prepared to learn how Brazil will set the standard for digital democracy<!--:--><!--:en--><p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Amar Ashar</strong></p>\n<span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">The ITS fellowship 2014 was a terrific opportunity for me to gain more insight into the Internet policy landscape in Brazil, and the significant contributions ITS has and continues to make to research, advocacy work, and education in the country. As a fellow, it was a privilege to have very open and off-the-record conversations with policymakers, regulators, company representatives, telecom agencies, and beyond ranging on issues from net neutrality to culture and intellectual property. The fellowship also served as a forum to present on the projects that the fellows were working on, and I learned a lot about their fields, and appreciated the opportunity for feedback on my work and to offer comments on theirs. I also enjoyed learning about the research and other projects ITS was undertaking, helping to consult on and guide the direction of those projects based on my own experience and knowledge.</span>\n\n<span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">Given the chance, I would absolutely apply for the fellowship again. The things I found the most useful during my time in Brazil were: (1) the field trips and meetings to Brasilia and San Paulo to learn more from the stakeholders involved in Marco Civil; (2) the briefings that Ronaldo, Carlos, Fabro, and others at ITS offered with respect to the most pressing Internet policy and legal issues in the country today (and the ones they are working on), and (3) the time and space built into the program to pursue our own independent and projects and work, with the opportunity to connect it with ITS\' work and its broader network.</span>\n\n<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">Primavera de Filippi</span></strong>\n\nIt was really great to meet all the people from ITS + the other fellows. It was great to learn about the projects that the ITS is currently working on and the trips to Brasília and São Paulo were really useful to learn more about the Brazilian system. Also, the meetings with key stakeholders and regulators were also extremely useful to better understand the process of policy making in Brazil. And… very nice atmosphere, the ITS is a wonderful place to work (I miss the sunny office) and lastly the opportunity to present our research at the Varanda was also great\n\n<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">Amalia Deloney</span></strong>\n\nIn short: great to meet everyone, office was accessible, visits were great (especially the Regulatory ones) and trips to Brazilia and São Paulo provided a lot of context.\n\n<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">Kate Krontiris</span></strong>\n\nI loved spending so much time with young people who are really changing their reality (ahem - I mean ITS staff).  You guys were inspiring. I really appreciated the unstructured time and freedom in Rio, when we weren\'t making site visits.  Perhaps you can be more explicit that that will happen, but I loved that it allowed us to take our own trips and plan around our own interests. I liked that my fellow peers had such different expertise sets and interests than I.  I learned a lot from them.\n\n<strong>Allison Burtch</strong>\n\nHave you ever wondered how the global telecommunications infrastructure system is connected? What rights do people have when social media is the only way they access the internet? How is it possible to crowd-source legislation? Rio de Janeiro is a fascinating place, and an epicenter for an in-depth look at development, gentrification, and digital access. The ITS staff is a brilliant group of writers, lawyers, policy makers and technologists. I would highly recommend applying to this residency, and be prepared to learn how Brazil will set the standard for digital democracy<!--:-->','ITS Fellows 2014 and what they said about their experience','','trash','closed','closed','','its-fellows-2014-and-what-they-said-about-their-experience','','','2015-02-04 21:05:05','2015-02-04 23:05:05','',0,'http://www.itsrio.org/?p=1260',0,'post','',0),(1298,1,'2015-03-21 12:44:20','2015-03-21 15:44:20','<!--:pt--><a href=\"www.facebook.com/ITSriodejaneiro\">Facebook</a>\n<a href=\"https://twitter.com/ITSriodejaneiro\">Twitter</a>\n<a href=\"www.youtube.com/itsriodejaneiro\">YouTube</a>\n<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/itsriodejaneiro/\">Instagram</a>\n<a href=\"https://medium.com/@ITSriodejaneiro\">Medium</a>\n<a href=\"http://www.brasilpost.com.br/instituto-de-tecnologia-e-sociedade/\">HuffPost Brasil</a>\n\n<!--:-->','ITS nas redes','','publish','closed','closed','','its-nas-redes','','','2015-03-21 12:44:20','2015-03-21 15:44:20','',0,'http://www.itsrio.org/?page_id=1298',0,'page','',0),(1301,1,'2015-03-23 16:04:54','2015-03-23 19:04:54','<!--:pt--><p dir=\"ltr\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-04a1bac5-565a-18ea-7c34-a642eadcfa52\"><strong>Repensado Cultura, Direito e Tecnologia<br />\n</strong><em>Curso de extensão ao vivo online</em></p>\n<p>O ITS reuniu o melhor time de professores especialistas em direito, cultura e tecnologia para quem quer dominar conhecimentos práticos nessas áreas, prontos para o futuro.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">O curso de extensão \"Repensando Cultura, Direito &amp; Tecnologia\"  busca estudar de modo abrangente as principais tendências e inovações que acontecem na relação entre direito, cultura e tecnologia.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Ele aborda temas como o Marco Civil da Internet, Direitos Autorais, Propaganda e Marketing, Lei Rouanet e Financiamento de Projetos Culturais, Crowdfunding, novas mídias, games e narrativas transmídia, dentre outros tópicos.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">O curso é aberto a profissionais, estudantes e pesquisadores de quaisquer áreas, incluindo gestores culturais, advogados, profissionais do terceiro setor, empresários e empreendedores culturais, jornalistas, designers, escritores, músicos, produtores e qualquer interessado em temas como economia criativa, direito e tecnologia atuando no Brasil e no exterior.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">As aulas são dadas ao vivo por cada professor pela internet, por meio da plataforma interativa do ITS.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Receberão certificado de participação os alunos que tiverem ao menos 75% de presença.</p>\n<p>Ao final do curso, será aplicada uma avaliação facultativa. Os dois alunos mais bem avaliados serão selecionados para o curso que o ITS oferece cada ano em parceria com a Universidade de Harvard.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.itsrio.org/2015/03/23/saiba-detalhes-do-curso-repensado-cultura-direito-e-tecnologia-2a-turma/\"><strong>INSCRIÇÕES E DETALHES</strong></a></p>\n\n<!-- INICIO FORMULARIO BOTAO PAGSEGURO -->\n<form action=\"https://pagseguro.uol.com.br/checkout/v2/cart.html?action=add\" method=\"post\">\n<!-- NÃO EDITE OS COMANDOS DAS LINHAS ABAIXO -->\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"itemCode\" value=\"7234DFC507077639944DDFA319EF7B71\" />\n<input type=\"image\" src=\"https://p.simg.uol.com.br/out/pagseguro/i/botoes/pagamentos/120x53-comprar.gif\" name=\"submit\" alt=\"Pague com PagSeguro - é rápido, grátis e seguro!\" />\n</form>\n<!-- FINAL FORMULARIO BOTAO PAGSEGURO --><!--:-->','Lançada 2a turma do Curso de Extensão Repensando Cultura, Direito & Tecnologia','','trash','closed','closed','','2aturmarepensando','','','2015-03-23 16:04:54','2015-03-23 19:04:54','',0,'http://www.itsrio.org/?p=1301',0,'post','',0),(1306,1,'2015-03-23 21:15:08','2015-03-24 00:15:08','<!--:pt--><p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"http://www.itsrio.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Post-institu-DEF.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-1319\" alt=\"Post institu DEF\" src=\"http://www.itsrio.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Post-institu-DEF-227x190.jpg\" width=\"227\" height=\"190\" /></a><strong>Repensando Cultura, Direito & Tecnologia</p>\n<p></strong><em>Curso de extensão ao vivo online - Inscrições encerradas</em></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">O Instituto de Tecnologia & Sociedade do Rio de Janeiro está lançando o curso de extensão <strong>Repensando Cultura, Direito & Tecnologia</strong> ao vivo e online. O curso que é sucesso no Rio de Janeiro, agora está aberto para alunos de todo o Brasil.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">O ITS reuniu o melhor time de professores especialistas em direito, cultura e tecnologia para quem quer dominar conhecimentos práticos nessas áreas, prontos para o futuro.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">O curso <strong>Repensando Cultura, Direito & Tecnologia</strong> busca estudar de modo abrangente as principais tendências e inovações que acontecem na relação entre direito, cultura e tecnologia.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Ele aborda temas como o Marco Civil da Internet, Direitos Autorais, Propaganda e Marketing, Lei Rouanet e Financiamento de Projetos Culturais, Crowdfunding, novas mídias, games e narrativas transmídia, dentre outros tópicos.</p>\n<p><strong>O que você não vai encontrar no nosso curso? </strong>Enrolação, divagação e conhecimentos desconectados da realidade prática do mercado. Você também não vai encontrar professores que não sabem do que estão falando ou não dominam completamente o tema. O time do ITS é formado por alguns dos mais reconhecidos professores e especialistas nos temas envolvendo direito, tecnologia e cultura do país. Confira abaixo.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em><strong>Qual o perfil dos alunos?</p>\n<p></strong></em>O curso é aberto para profissionais, estudantes e pesquisadores de quaisquer áreas, incluindo gestores culturais, advogados, profissionais do terceiro setor, empresários e empreendedores culturais, jornalistas, designers, escritores, músicos, produtores e qualquer interessado em temas como economia criativa, direito e tecnologia atuando no Brasil e no exterior.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em><strong>Qual tipo de certificado é oferecido?</p>\n<p></strong></em>Receberão certificado de participação com carga horária de 45 horas os alunos que tiverem ao menos 75% de presença. Ao final do curso, será aplicada uma avaliação facultativa. Os dois alunos mais bem avaliados serão selecionados para o curso que o ITS oferece em parceria com a Universidade de Harvard em Janeiro de 2016.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Qual o calendário do curso?</p>\n<p></strong></em>Início: 11 de Maio</p>\n<p>Aulas: Segundas e Quartas, das 19h às 21h.</p>\n<p>Encerramento: 29 de Junho</p>\n<p><strong>Valor:</p>\n<p></strong>Inscrições a partir de 21 de abril: R$ 1480,00 em até 15x.</p>\n<p>Vagas: 30</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Local:</strong></p>\n<p>Online e ao vivo, através  de plataforma interativa do ITS a ser disponibilizada aos alunos.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Inscrição:</strong></p>\n<p>A matrícula é feita por meio do PagSeguro, que permite efetuar o pagamento do curso em até 15 parcelas, utilizando o seu cartão de crédito. Qualquer dúvida, inclusive com relação à forma de pagamento, entre em contato com o ITS pelo nosso telefone ou pelo e-mail <a href=\"mailto:cursos@itsrio.org\">cursos@itsrio.org</a></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-db8eede0-5640-3944-9ca9-d98249254c6e\">Mais informações:</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://www.itsrio.org/sobre-o-its/\">Sobre o ITS </a></strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Temas a serem abordados nas aulas:</strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">- Repensando a cultura – cultura, contracultura e cibercultura</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">- Teoria da cultura e mídias digitais</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">- Economia criativa</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">- Financiamento da cultura</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">- Crowdfunding e novos modelos de financiamento</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">- Direitos autorais aplicado à cultura e a modernização  da lei brasileira</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">- Marco Civil, Direitos de imagem, privacidade e honra e as obras culturais</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">- Narrativas Transmídia e Games</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">- O movimento maker – faça você mesmo!</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">- A internet das coisas e o futuro da conectividade</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">- Tecnologia, democracia e as transformações sociais</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Professores:</strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"http://www.itsrio.org/sobre-o-its/equipe/#elianecosta\"><strong>Eliane Costa</strong></p>\n<p></a>Doutoranda na UFRJ/HCTE, foi por dez anos gerente de patrocínio da Petrobrás. Autora do livro Jangada Digital, sobre as políticas públicas do Ministério da Cultura, na gestão Gilberto Gil, voltadas à Cultura Digital, especialmente no âmbito do Programa Cultura Viva / Pontos de Cultura.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"http://www.itsrio.org/sobre-o-its/equipe/#ronaldolemos\"><strong>Ronaldo Lemos</strong></p>\n<p></a>Doutor pela USP, professor da graduação e da pós-graduação da UERJ. Pesquisador visitante do MIT Midia Lab. Diretor do projeto Creative Commons no Brasil e co-fundador do projeto Overmundo. Apresenta o programa Navegador, na Globonews. Diretor do ITS.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"http://www.itsrio.org/sobre-o-its/equipe/#carlosaffonso\"><strong>Carlos Affonso Souza</strong></p>\n<p></a>Doutor pela UERJ, professor da graduação e da pós-graduação da UERJ. Pesquisador Visitante do Information Society Project, da Faculdade de Direito da Universidade de Yale. Diretor do ITS.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"http://www.itsrio.org/sobre-o-its/equipe/#sergiobranco\"><strong>Sérgio Branco</strong></p>\n<p></a>Doutor em Direito Civil pela UERJ. Pós-graduado em cinema documentário pela FGV. Autor dos livros “Direitos Autorais na Internet e o Uso de Obras Alheias”, “O Domínio Público no Direito Autoral Brasileiro” e “O que é Creative Commons?”. Diretor do ITS.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"http://www.itsrio.org/sobre-o-its/equipe/#juliananolasco\"><strong>Juliana Nolasco</strong></p>\n<p></a>Mestre pela FGV, coordenadora geral de economia da cultura e estudos culturais do Ministério da Cultura durante o governo do Presidente Lula. Diretora executiva do ITS.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"http://br.linkedin.com/in/gabiagustini\"><strong>Gabriela Agustini</strong></p>\n<p></a>Sócia e Diretora de Inovação no Templo, espaço de empreendedorismo situado no Rio de Janeiro, onde coordena o Olabi, espaço voltado para a apropriação de novas tecnologias. É professora de cultura e tecnologia na Universidade Cândido Mendes e na FGV Rio e consultora do Ministério da Cultura via Unesco na área de economia criativa.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"http://br.linkedin.com/pub/bruno-lewicki/84/302/237\"><strong>Bruno Lewicki</strong></p>\n<p></a>Doutor pela UERJ. Trabalhou na Câmara dos Deputados acompanhando a reforma da Lei de Direitos Autorais e atuou como vice-presidente da Comissão de Direitos Autorais da OAB-RJ (2010-2012).</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"http://www.itsrio.org/sobre-o-its/equipe/#fabrosteibel\"><strong>Fabro Steibel</strong></p>\n<p></a>Pós-doutor em comunicações. Professor da ESPM-RJ. Relator (independent researcher) da Open Government Partnership no Brasil e membro do ITS.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"http://www.itsrio.org/sobre-o-its/equipe/#arthurprotasio\"><strong>Arthur Protasio</strong></p>\n<p></a>Mestre em Design com graduação em Direito e domínio adicional em Mídias Digitais pela PUC-Rio​. Designer de narrativas, fundador da produtora Fableware e especialista em criar histórias para diferentes mídias, desde livros, jogos, TV até parques de diversão. Membro do ITS.</p>\n<!--:--><!--:en--><a href=\"http://www.itsrio.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/FB_Serie_New_2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-1304\" alt=\"FB_Serie_New_2\" src=\"http://www.itsrio.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/FB_Serie_New_2-227x190.jpg\" width=\"227\" height=\"190\" /></a>\n<h1>Repensado Cultura, Direito e Tecnologia</h1>\n<h3>Curso de extensão</h3>\nO Instituto de Tecnologia & Sociedade do Rio de Janeiro lança a 2a turma do curso “Repensado Cultura, Direito & Tecnologia”.\n\nO curso Repensando Cultura, Direito & Tecnologia de modo abrangente as principais tendências e inovações que acontece na relação entre direito, cultura e tecnologia.\n\n<strong>Fatos sobre o curso:</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">A 1a turma do curso foi um sucesso, e aconteceu na sede do ITS, no Rio de Janeiro </span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">A 2a turma do curso está aberta, e agora acontece online, ao vivo, e está aberta para alunos de todo o Brasil.</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">Os professores reunidos são experts em áreas exponentes de direito, cultura e tecnologia</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">O curso é voltado para domínio de conhecimentos práticos, voltados para aplicação no dia-a-dia.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<strong style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">O curso aborda temas como:</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>Marco Civil da Internet</li>\n	<li>Direitos Autorais</li>\n	<li>Publicidade e redes sociais</li>\n	<li>Lei Rouanet e Financiamento de Projetos Culturais</li>\n	<li>Crowdfunding</li>\n	<li>Games e narrativas transmídia</li>\n	<li>Muitos outros.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Qual o perfil dos alunos?</strong>\n\nO curso é aberto para profissionais, estudantes e pesquisadores de diversas áreas, incluindo gestores culturais, profissionais do terceiro setor, empresários e empreendedores culturais, jornalistas, designers, escritores, músicos, produtores e qualquer interessado em economia criativa, atuando no Brasil e no exterior.\n\n<strong>Qual o calendário do curso?</strong>\n\nAs aulas começam no dia 11 de maio e vão até 29 de junho de 2015. As aulas serão dadas ao vivo, por cada professor pela internet, como total interatividade entre alunos e professores, por meio de plataforma interativa fornecida pelo ITS.\n\n<strong>Qual tipo de certificado é oferecido?</strong>\n\nAo final do curso será emitido certificado para os alunos, mediante avaliação final. Os dois melhores alunos serão indicados para o curso que o ITS oferecerá em parceria com a Universidade de Harvard, em janeiro de 2016.\n\n<strong>Detalhes do curso:</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">Calendário: de 11 de Maio a 29 de Junho</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">Horário: Segundas e Quartas, das 19h às 21h (aulas online, que acontecem nesses horários).</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">Valor:  </span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">R$ 1.320,00  (preço promocional até 20, abril). A partir de 21 de abril, R$ 1.480,00</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">Formas de pagamento: PagSeguro, em até 15x. Link abaixo.</span></li>\n	<li>Vagas: 30</li>\n	<li>Local: Online e ao vivo, através de plataforma interativa do ITS.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Como realizar inscrição?</strong>\n\nA matrícula é feita por meio do PagSeguro, que permite efetuar o pagamento do curso em até 15 parcelas, utilizando o seu cartão de crédito. Qualquer dúvida, inclusive com relação à forma de pagamento, entre em contato com o ITS pelo nosso telefone ou pelo e-mail cursos@itsrio.org\n\n<!-- INICIO FORMULARIO BOTAO PAGSEGURO -->\n\n<form action=\"https://pagseguro.uol.com.br/checkout/v2/payment.html\" method=\"post\"><input type=\"hidden\" name=\"code\" value=\"D47047F49494781AA40FEF8867405481\" />\n<input type=\"image\" alt=\"Pague com PagSeguro - é rápido, grátis e seguro!\" name=\"submit\" src=\"https://p.simg.uol.com.br/out/pagseguro/i/botoes/pagamentos/120x53-pagar.gif\" /></form><!-- FINAL FORMULARIO BOTAO PAGSEGURO -->\n<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">Temas das aulas:</span></strong>\n<ol>\n	<li>Repensando a cultura – cultura, contracultura e cibercultura</li>\n	<li>Teoria da cultura e mídias digitais</li>\n	<li>Economia criativa</li>\n	<li>Financiamento da cultura</li>\n	<li>Crowdfunding e novos modelos de financiamento</li>\n	<li>Direitos autorais aplicado à cultura e a modernização da lei brasileira</li>\n	<li>Marco Civil, Direitos de imagem, privacidade e honra e as obras culturais</li>\n	<li>Narrativas Transmídia e Games</li>\n	<li>O movimento maker – faça você mesmo!</li>\n	<li>A internet das coisas e o futuro da conectividade</li>\n	<li>Tecnologia, democracia e as transformações sociais</li>\n</ol>\n<strong>Professores:</strong>\n<em><strong>Eliane Costa</strong></em>\nDoutoranda na UFRJ/HCTE, foi por dez anos gerente de patrocínio da Petrobrás. Autora do livro Jangada Digital, sobre as políticas públicas do Ministério da Cultura, na gestão Gilberto Gil, voltadas à Cultura Digital, especialmente no âmbito do Programa Cultura Viva / Pontos de Cultura.\n\n<em><strong>Ronaldo Lemos</strong></em>\nDoutor pela USP, professor da graduação e da pós-graduação da UERJ. Pesquisador visitante do MIT Midia Lab. Diretor do projeto Creative Commons no Brasil e co-fundador do projeto Overmundo. Apresenta o programa Navegador, na Globonews. Diretor do ITS.\n\n<em><strong>Carlos Affonso Souza</strong></em>\nDoutor pela UERJ, professor da graduação e da pós-graduação da UERJ. Pesquisador Visitante do Information Society Project, da Faculdade de Direito da Universidade de Yale. Diretor do ITS.\n\n<em><strong>Sérgio Branco</strong></em>\nDoutor em Direito Civil pela UERJ. Pós-graduado em cinema documentário pela FGV. Autor dos livros “Direitos Autorais na Internet e o Uso de Obras Alheias”, “O Domínio Público no Direito Autoral Brasileiro” e “O que é Creative Commons?”. Diretor do ITS.\n\n<em><strong>Juliana Nolasco</strong></em>\nMestre pela FGV, coordenadora geral de economia da cultura e estudos culturais do Ministério da Cultura durante o governo do Presidente Lula. Diretora executiva do ITS.\n\n<em><strong>Gabriela Agustini</strong></em>\nSócia e Diretora de Inovação no Templo, espaço de empreendedorismo situado no Rio de Janeiro, onde coordena o Olabi, espaço voltado para a apropriação de novas tecnologias. É professora de cultura e tecnologia na Universidade Cândido Mendes e na FGV Rio e consultora do Ministério da Cultura via Unesco na área de economia criativa.\n\n<em><strong>Bruno Lewicki</strong></em>\nDoutor pela UERJ. Trabalhou na Câmara dos Deputados acompanhando a reforma da Lei de Direitos Autorais e atuou como vice-presidente da Comissão de Direitos Autorais da OAB-RJ (2010-2012).\n\n<em><strong>Fabro Steibel</strong></em>\nPós-doutor em comunicações. Professor da ESPM-RJ. Relator (independent researcher) da Open Government Partnership no Brasil e membro do ITS.\n\n<em><strong>Arthur Protasio</strong></em>\nMestre em Design com graduação em Direito e domínio adicional em Mídias Digitais pela PUC-Rio​. Designer de narrativas, fundador da produtora Fableware e especialista em criar histórias para diferentes mídias, desde livros, jogos, TV até parques de diversão. Membro do ITS.<!--:-->','Curso Repensando Cultura, Direito & Tecnologia','','trash','closed','closed','','saiba-detalhes-do-curso-repensado-cultura-direito-e-tecnologia-2a-turma','','','2015-03-23 21:15:08','2015-03-24 00:15:08','',0,'http://www.itsrio.org/?p=1306',0,'post','',0),(1345,1,'2015-04-07 12:27:25','2015-04-07 15:27:25','<!--:pt-->The Institute of Technology and Society - ITS announces the fellows who will join the community in the second semester of 2015, starting a long-term tradition of providing a home for some of the most incisive minds in law, technology, and social science, alongside brilliant entrepreneurs and activists.\n\nOur Global Fellows will spend four weeks in Brazil and have the unique opportunity to work with the team who conceived and developed the landmark “Marco Civil” legislation, a bill protecting fundamental rights, including privacy, net neutrality and freedom of expression, approved as law in Brazil in April 2014. ITS will offer the opportunity to work with research in the five broad areas, namely:\n<ul>\n	<li>Law, democracy and technology (dealing with topics such as civil engagement, online participation, and others);</li>\n	<li>Access to technology, justice and human rights (dealing with topics such as connectivity, accessibility, digital divide and others);</li>\n	<li>Internet regulation and Internet governance;</li>\n	<li>Privacy and data protection (dealing with topics such as big data, anti-survailance, data protection and mass surveilance);</li>\n	<li>Rethinking culture, media and education (working with topics such as intelectual property, digital entrepreneurship, art &amp; technology, online teaching, and others).</li>\n</ul>\nITS has prepared an intensive 4-week program for our fellows, which includes visits to the biggest technology companies operating in Brazil, the Brazilian Internet Steering Committee (CGI.br) and visits to São Paulo and Brasília, including representatives from the Ministry of Justice, Ministry of Culture and Congressmen who are advocating for policies related to internet and technology.\n\nDuring their stay, selected fellows will be expected to:\n\nPresent at least one public seminar, organized in partnership with ITS. Suggested topics can include: broadband and access policy, content regulation, copyright and creativity, consumer privacy, open government, government surveillance, data security, data innovation, freedom of expression, democracy and technology and human rights;\nTo publish at least one article or webpost about their experience as a fellow in Brazil;\nTo collaborate with the ITS team and its projects;\n\nJoining the community in 2015/2 as ITS fellows:\n\nDaniel Arnaudo\nEmy Tseng\nFlorian Martin Bariteau\nGemma Galdon Clave\nPayal Arora\nRoxana Radu\n\nWelcome to ITS!\n\nAbout ITS:\n\nThe mission of the Institute for Technology &amp; Society of Rio de Janeiro is to ensure that Brazil responds creatively and appropriately to the opportunities provided by technology in the digital age, and that the potential benefits are broadly shared across society. Through its legal, social, economic and cultural dimensions of technology, ITS advocates for legal and regulatory measures which protect privacy, freedom of expression and access to knowledge. ITS also offers innovative training and education to individuals and institutions willing to understand the promises and challenges of new technologies. Lastly, ITS aims to strengthen the voice of Brazil, Latin America and the Global South in international debates on technology and its regulation.<!--:--><!--:en-->The Institute of Technology and Society - ITS announces the fellows who will join the community in the second semester of 2015, starting a long-term tradition of providing a home for some of the most incisive minds in law, technology, and social science, alongside brilliant entrepreneurs and activists.\n\nOur Global Fellows will spend four weeks in Brazil and have the unique opportunity to work with the team who conceived and developed the landmark “Marco Civil” legislation, a bill protecting fundamental rights, including privacy, net neutrality and freedom of expression, approved as law in Brazil in April 2014. ITS will offer the opportunity to work with research in the five broad areas, namely:\n<ul>\n	<li>Law, democracy and technology (dealing with topics such as civil engagement, online participation, and others);</li>\n	<li>Access to technology, justice and human rights (dealing with topics such as connectivity, accessibility, digital divide and others);</li>\n	<li>Internet regulation and Internet governance;</li>\n	<li>Privacy and data protection (dealing with topics such as big data, anti-survailance, data protection and mass surveilance);</li>\n	<li>Rethinking culture, media and education (working with topics such as intelectual property, digital entrepreneurship, art &amp; technology, online teaching, and others).</li>\n</ul>\nITS has prepared an intensive 4-week program for our fellows, which includes visits to the biggest technology companies operating in Brazil, the Brazilian Internet Steering Committee (CGI.br) and visits to São Paulo and Brasília, including representatives from the Ministry of Justice, Ministry of Culture and Congressmen who are advocating for policies related to internet and technology.\n\nDuring their stay, selected fellows will be expected to:\n<ul>\n	<li>Present at least one public seminar, organized in partnership with ITS. Suggested topics can include: broadband and access policy, content regulation, copyright and creativity, consumer privacy, open government, government surveillance, data security, data innovation, freedom of expression, democracy and technology and human rights;</li>\n	<li>To publish at least one article or webpost about their experience as a fellow in Brazil;</li>\n	<li>To collaborate with the ITS team and its projects;</li>\n</ul>\nJoining the community in 2015/2 as ITS fellows:\n<ul>\n	<li>Daniel Arnaudo</li>\n	<li>Emy Tseng</li>\n	<li>Florian Martin Bariteau</li>\n	<li>Gemma Galdon Clave</li>\n	<li>Payal Arora</li>\n	<li>Roxana Radu</li>\n</ul>\nWelcome to ITS!\n\nAbout ITS:\n\nThe mission of the Institute for Technology &amp; Society of Rio de Janeiro is to ensure that Brazil responds creatively and appropriately to the opportunities provided by technology in the digital age, and that the potential benefits are broadly shared across society. Through its legal, social, economic and cultural dimensions of technology, ITS advocates for legal and regulatory measures which protect privacy, freedom of expression and access to knowledge. ITS also offers innovative training and education to individuals and institutions willing to understand the promises and challenges of new technologies. Lastly, ITS aims to strengthen the voice of Brazil, Latin America and the Global South in international debates on technology and its regulation.<!--:-->','Bem-vindos fellows ITS 2015','','trash','closed','closed','','bem-vindos-fellows-its-2015','','','2015-04-07 12:27:25','2015-04-07 15:27:25','',0,'http://www.itsrio.org/?p=1345',0,'post','',0),(1488,1,'2015-06-11 16:48:29','2015-06-11 19:48:29','<!--:pt--><strong>Coordenação de Comunicação - ITS</strong>\n\nimprensa@itsrio.org\n+55 (21) 3486-0390\n\nVictor Vicente\nAssistente de Comunicação\nvvicente@itsrio.org\n+55 (21) 982 627 782\n<!--:-->','Imprensa','','publish','closed','closed','','imprensa','','','2015-06-11 16:48:29','2015-06-11 19:48:29','',0,'http://itsrio.org/?page_id=1488',0,'page','',0),(1496,3,'2015-06-18 16:29:17','2015-06-18 19:29:17','','1Daniel Arnaudo-editada','','inherit','open','open','','1daniel-arnaudo-editada','','','2015-06-18 16:29:17','2015-06-18 19:29:17','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/1Daniel-Arnaudo-editada.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1497,3,'2015-06-18 16:29:23','2015-06-18 19:29:23','','2Emy Tseng-editada','','inherit','open','open','','2emy-tseng-editada','','','2015-06-18 16:29:23','2015-06-18 19:29:23','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/2Emy-Tseng-editada.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1498,3,'2015-06-18 16:29:26','2015-06-18 19:29:26','','3Florian Martin Bariteau-editada','','inherit','open','open','','3florian-martin-bariteau-editada','','','2015-06-18 16:29:26','2015-06-18 19:29:26','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/3Florian-Martin-Bariteau-editada.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1499,3,'2015-06-18 16:29:30','2015-06-18 19:29:30','','4Gemma Clavell-editada','','inherit','open','open','','4gemma-clavell-editada','','','2015-06-18 16:29:30','2015-06-18 19:29:30','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/4Gemma-Clavell-editada.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1500,3,'2015-06-18 16:29:32','2015-06-18 19:29:32','','5Karima Smouk-editada','','inherit','open','open','','5karima-smouk-editada','','','2015-06-18 16:29:32','2015-06-18 19:29:32','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/5Karima-Smouk-editada.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1501,3,'2015-06-18 16:29:34','2015-06-18 19:29:34','','6Payal Arora-editada','','inherit','open','open','','6payal-arora-editada','','','2015-06-18 16:29:34','2015-06-18 19:29:34','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/6Payal-Arora-editada.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1502,3,'2015-06-18 16:29:36','2015-06-18 19:29:36','','7Roxana Radu-editada','','inherit','open','open','','7roxana-radu-editada','','','2015-06-18 16:29:36','2015-06-18 19:29:36','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/7Roxana-Radu-editada.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1518,3,'2015-07-01 14:07:13','2015-07-01 17:07:13','<!--:pt--><p><strong>DIREITOS AUTORAIS NO MUNDO CONECTADO<br />\n</strong><em>Curso ao vivo online - Inscrições encerradas</em></p>\n<p>O Instituto de Tecnologia & Sociedade do Rio de Janeiro reuniu o melhor time de professores especialistas para tratar de um dos temas mais importantes do mundo atual: <strong>os direitos autorais.</strong> O curso foi feito para quem quer dominar <strong>conhecimentos práticos sobre o tema</strong>, no momento em que a internet e a tecnologia digital tornam a circulação de obras mais fácil, trazendo também novos desafios.</p>\n<p>O curso <strong>Direitos Autorais no Mundo Conectado</strong> buscou debater de modo abrangente as principais tendências e inovações relacionadas à proteção dos direitos autorais no contexto dos avanços tecnológicos.</p>\n<p><strong>Nosso curso apresentou de forma clara e didática todos os fundamentos do direito autoral.</strong> Nele, discutimos como os direitos autorais configuram um sistema internacional, quais são os direitos dos titulares das obras, em que circunstâncias as criações autorais podem existir sem autorização prévia dos autores, principais modelos de contratos e licenças autorais. O curso trabalhou também com os temas mais quentes e discutidos do momento, tais como streaming, biografias não autorizadas, ECAD e o pagamento de direitos, o processo de modernização da lei de direitos autorais e uso de obras nas redes sociais.</p>\n<p><strong>E o que você não vai encontrar no nosso curso?</strong> Enrolação, divagação e conhecimentos desconectados da realidade prática do mercado. Você também não vai encontrar professores que não sabem do que estão falando ou não dominam completamente o tema. O time do ITS é formado por alguns dos mais reconhecidos professores e especialistas em direitos autorais do Brasil, que atuam no tema em colaboração com diversas instituições acadêmicas internacionais, incluindo a universidade de Harvard. </p>\n<p><strong>Qual o perfil dos alunos?</strong><br />\nO curso é aberto para profissionais de todas as áreas, incluindo advogados, juízes, promotores culturais, gestores do terceiro setor, empresários, jornalistas, pesquisadores, estudantes, artistas, músicos, escritores, editores, fotógrafos, designers e qualquer interessado em saber na prática como lidar com os direitos autorais. </p>\n<p><strong>Qual tipo de certificado é oferecido?</strong><br />\nRecebem certificado de participação os alunos que tiverem ao menos 75% de presença aferida de acordo com o acesso à plataforma do curso.</p>\n<p><strong>Qual o calendário do curso?</strong><br />\nInício: 25 de agosto<br />\nAulas: Terças e quintas, das 19h às 21h<br />\nEncerramento: 24 de setembro</p>\n<p><strong>Valor:</strong><br />\nInscrições a partir de 01 de agosto: R$ 1.150,00 à vista ou em até 12x de acordo com as regras do PagSeguro</p>\n<p><strong>Vagas:</strong> 40</p>\n<p><strong>Local:</strong><br />\nSomente ao vivo online, por meio de plataforma interativa do ITS a ser disponibilizada aos alunos.</p>\n<p><strong>Inscrição:</strong><br />\nA matrícula é feita por meio do PagSeguro, que permite efetuar o pagamento do curso em até 12 parcelas, utilizando o seu cartão de crédito. Qualquer dúvida, inclusive com relação à forma de pagamento, entre em contato com o ITS pelo nosso telefone ou pelo e-mail <a class=\"__cf_email__\" href=\"/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection\" data-cfemail=\"21425453524e526148555253484e0f4e5346\">[email protected]</a><script data-cfhash=\'f9e31\' type=\"text/javascript\">/* <![CDATA[ */!function(t,e,r,n,c,a,p){try{t=document.currentScript||function(){for(t=document.getElementsByTagName(\'script\'),e=t.length;e--;)if(t[e].getAttribute(\'data-cfhash\'))return t[e]}();if(t&&(c=t.previousSibling)){p=t.parentNode;if(a=c.getAttribute(\'data-cfemail\')){for(e=\'\',r=\'0x\'+a.substr(0,2)|0,n=2;a.length-n;n+=2)e+=\'%\'+(\'0\'+(\'0x\'+a.substr(n,2)^r).toString(16)).slice(-2);p.replaceChild(document.createTextNode(decodeURIComponent(e)),c)}p.removeChild(t)}}catch(u){}}()/* ]]> */</script></p>\n<p><strong>Temas abordados nas aulas:</strong><br />\n* Introdução e história dos direitos autorais; o sistema internacional; convenção de Berna; a lei brasileira de direitos autorais.<br />\n* Quem é autor? Autoria e titularidade; pessoas físicas e jurídicas; coautoria.<br />\n* Os direitos autorais; direitos morais e direitos de personalidade; direitos patrimoniais e exploração econômica da criação.<br />\n* Obras protegidas e não protegidas; extensão da lei; a proteção da moda; a proteção de ideias.<br />\n* Usos legalmente autorizados; limitações aos direitos autorais; fair use e sistema norte-americano; usos livres e domínio público<br />\n* Os contratos relativos aos direitos autorais; licença e cessão; as cláusulas contratuais; revisão dos contratos; licenças públicas gerais.<br />\n* Modernização da lei de direitos autorais; a regulação da gestão coletiva e do ECAD pela lei brasileira.<br />\n* Biografias; direito de imagem, privacidade e honra.<br />\n* Os direitos autorais no streaming; remix e divulgação de obras em redes sociais. </p>\n<p><strong>Professores:</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Ronaldo Lemos</strong><br />\nDoutor pela USP, professor da graduação e da pós-graduação da UERJ. Pesquisador visitante do MIT Midia Lab. Diretor do projeto Creative Commons no Brasil e co-fundador do projeto Overmundo. Apresenta o programa Navegador, na Globonews. Diretor do ITS.</p>\n<p><strong>Carlos Affonso Souza</strong><br />\nDoutor pela UERJ, professor da graduação e da pós-graduação da UERJ. Pesquisador Visitante do Information Society Project, da Faculdade de Direito da Universidade de Yale. Diretor do ITS.</p>\n<p><strong>Sérgio Branco</strong><br />\nDoutor em Direito Civil pela UERJ. Pós-graduado em cinema documentário pela FGV. Autor dos livros “Direitos Autorais na Internet e o Uso de Obras Alheias”, “O Domínio Público no Direito Autoral Brasileiro” e “O que é Creative Commons?”. Diretor do ITS.</p>\n<p><strong>Bruno Lewicki</strong><br />\nDoutor pela UERJ. Trabalhou na Câmara dos Deputados acompanhando a reforma da Lei de Direitos Autorais e atuou como vice-presidente da Comissão de Direitos Autorais da OAB-RJ (2010-2012).</p>\n<p><strong>Leonardo Morel</strong><br />\nMúsico profissional, analista do mercado musical latino-americano para a empresa inglesa Midia Research e autor dos livros “Música e tecnologia” (Azougue, 2010) e “Monobloco: uma biografia” (Azougue, 2015). É docente do MBA em Bens Culturais da Fundação Getúlio Vargas-Rio, pesquisador do Núcleo de Estudos e Pesquisa em Direito, Arte e Cultura (NEDAC – UFRJ) e mestrando em Políticas Públicas, Estratégias e Desenvolvimento (PPED), pela Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro (UFRJ).</p>\n<p><strong>Mario Viola</strong><br />\nAdvogado, Doutor em Direito e Master of Research pelo European University Institute, na Itália. Mestre em Direito Civil e Especialista em Direito do Consumidor pela UERJ e em Direito Privado pela UFF.</p>\n<!--:-->','Abertas as inscrições para o curso \'Direitos Autorais no Mundo Conectado\'','','publish','closed','closed','','abertas-as-inscricoes-para-o-curso-direitos-autorais-no-mundo-conectado','','','2015-07-01 14:07:13','2015-07-01 17:07:13','',0,'http://itsrio.org/?p=1518',0,'cursos_ctp','',0),(1549,3,'2015-07-01 14:49:45','2015-07-01 17:49:45','','Institucional_semData','','inherit','open','open','','institucional_semdata','','','2015-07-01 14:49:45','2015-07-01 17:49:45','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Institucional_semData.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1551,1,'2015-07-01 15:23:52','2015-07-01 18:23:52','<!--:pt--><strong>O MARCO CIVIL DA INTERNET E SUA APLICAÇÃO</strong>\n<em>Curso ao vivo online - Inscrições abertas até 17 de agosto</em>\n\nO Instituto de Tecnologia & Sociedade do Rio de Janeiro está lançando o curso de extensão ao vivo online <strong>O Marco Civil da Internet E Sua Aplicação</strong>. Ele será ministrado pelo melhor time de professores especialistas no Marco Civil, dentre eles, alguns dos idealizadores do processo de criação da lei.\n\nUm ano após o projeto do Marco Civil da Internet ter se tornado a Lei 12.965/2014, <strong>é hora de discutir sua aplicação e como o Marco Civil tornou-se referência</strong> para advogados, juízes, promotores, empresas de tecnologia e qualquer pessoa interessada em inovação em nosso país.  \n\nO curso <strong>Marco Civil da Internet e Sua Aplicação</strong> irá abordar temas como neutralidade da rede, privacidade, responsabilidade civil, proteção de dados pessoais e outras matérias reguladas por essa importante lei, sempre analisando as principais posições doutrinárias e decisões dos tribunais em que a Lei 12.965/2014 vem sendo aplicada.\n\n<strong>O que você não vai encontrar no nosso curso?</strong> Enrolação, divagação e conhecimentos desconectados da realidade prática do mercado. Você também não vai encontrar professores que não sabem do que estão falando ou não dominam completamente o tema. O time do ITS é formado por alguns dos mais reconhecidos professores e especialistas no Marco Civil da Internet. \n\n<strong>Qual o perfil dos alunos?\n</strong>O curso é destinado a advogados, juízes, promotores, gestores do terceiro setor, empresários, jornalistas, pesquisadores, empresários, inovadores, estudantes e qualquer interessado em saber como o Marco Civil da Internet deve ser aplicado em termos práticos, o que ele prevê, qual sua importância para a inovação e como ele vem sendo tratado pelo Poder Judiciário brasileiro.\n\n<strong>Qual tipo de certificado é oferecido?\n</strong>Receberão certificado de conclusão os alunos que tiverem ao menos 75% de presença aferida de acordo com o acesso à plataforma do curso.. \n\n<strong>Qual o calendário do curso?\n</strong>Início: 17 de agosto\nAulas: Segundas e Quartas, das 19h às 21h.\nEncerramento: 16 de setembro\n\n<strong>Valor:</strong>\nA partir de 01 de agosto: R$ 1.290,00 à vista ou em até 12x de acordo com as regras do PagSeguro\n\n<strong>Vagas:</strong> 40\n\n<strong>Local:\n</strong>Somente ao vivo online, por meio da plataforma interativa do ITS a ser disponibilizada aos alunos.\n\n<strong>Inscrição:\n</strong>A matrícula é feita por meio do PagSeguro, que permite efetuar o pagamento do curso em até 12 parcelas, utilizando o seu cartão de crédito. Qualquer dúvida, inclusive em relação à forma de pagamento, entre em contato com o ITS pelo nosso telefone ou pelo e-mail cursos@itsrio.org\n\n<strong>Temas a serem abordados nas aulas:\n</strong>\n* A história do Marco Civil e sua construção: a necessidade de regulamentação da internet; os principais debates da consulta pública; a redação final do texto; as divergências que antecederam sua aprovação no Congresso Nacional.\n* Princípios do Marco Civil: os novos princípios incorporados ao ordenamento jurídico brasileiro; a Constituição Federal de 1988 e o Marco Civil; a aplicação prática dos princípios elencados pela 12.965/2014.\n* Privacidade no Marco Civil: a privacidade como direito constitucionalmente protegido; a privacidade diante da inovação tecnológica; privacidade e internet; como se adaptar às mudanças relativas à proteção da privacidade pelo Marco Civil; responsabilidade civil; análise de decisões judiciais.\n* Proteção de dados pessoais: a proteção de dados pessoais e a tecnologia; dados pessoais e sua proteção pelo Marco Civil; big data: conceito, limites, possibilidades; o anteprojeto de lei de proteção de dados pessoais.\n* Liberdade de expressão e remoção de conteúdo: liberdade de expressão como direito constitucionalmente protegido; as regras do Marco Civil para remoção de conteúdo; a proteção da intimidade; a proteção dos direitos autorais; responsabilidade civil.\n* Neutralidade da rede: importância; a proteção pelo Marco Civil; regulamentação; zero rating.\n* Proteção dos direitos humanos e o Marco Civil: a regulação internacional dos direitos humanos; direitos humanos e tecnologia; a proteção dos direitos humanos pelo Marco Civil.\n* Governo aberto: práticas de governo aberto em âmbito internacional e nacional; democracia participativa direta; melhores práticas de governo aberto; iniciativas posteriores ao Marco Civil.\n\n<strong>Professores:</strong>\n\n<strong>Deputado Alessandro Molon </strong><em>(aula magna)</em> \n\n<strong>Ronaldo Lemos</strong>\nDoutor pela USP, professor da graduação e da pós-graduação da UERJ. Pesquisador visitante do MIT Midia Lab. Diretor do projeto Creative Commons no Brasil e co-fundador do projeto Overmundo. Apresenta o programa Navegador, na Globonews. Diretor do ITS.\n\n<strong>Carlos Affonso Souza</strong>\nDoutor pela UERJ, professor da graduação e da pós-graduação da UERJ. Pesquisador Visitante do Information Society Project, da Faculdade de Direito da Universidade de Yale. Diretor do ITS.\n\n<strong>Marcel Leonardi</strong>\nBacharel, Mestre e Doutor em Direito pela USP, com pós-doutorado pela Berkeley Law. Autor de \"Responsabilidade Civil dos Provedores de Serviços de Internet\", \"Tutela e Privacidade na Internet\" e co-autor de \"Responsabilidade Civil na Internet e nos demais meios de comunicação\". Professor da FGV Direito SP. Diretor de Políticas Públicas do Google no Brasil.\n\n<strong>Mario Viola</strong>\nAdvogado, Doutor em Direito e Master of Research pelo European University Institute, na Itália. Mestre em Direito Civil e Especialista em Direito do Consumidor pela UERJ e Especialista em Direito Privado pela UFF.\n\n<strong>Fabro Steibel\n</strong>Pós-doutor em comunicações. Professor da ESPM-RJ. Relator (independent researcher) da Open Government Partnership no Brasil e membro do ITS.\n\n<strong>Celina Bottino</strong>\nAdvogada, mestre em direitos humanos pela Universidade de Harvard e coordenadora de projetos do ITS. Especialista em direitos humanos e tecnologia. <!--:-->','ITS abre inscrições para o curso \'O Marco Civil da Internet e Sua Aplicação\'','','publish','closed','closed','','its-abre-inscricoes-para-o-curso-o-marco-civil-da-internet-com-seus-idealizadores','','','2015-07-01 15:23:52','2015-07-01 18:23:52','',0,'http://itsrio.org/?p=1551',0,'cursos_ctp','',0),(1574,3,'2015-07-01 17:14:06','2015-07-01 20:14:06','','Curso Direitos Autorais site ITS_home_projetos','','inherit','open','open','','curso-direitos-autorais-site-its_home_projetos','','','2015-07-01 17:14:06','2015-07-01 20:14:06','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Curso-Direitos-Autorais-site-ITS_home_projetos.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1579,3,'2015-07-01 17:47:43','2015-07-01 20:47:43','','Curso Direitos Autorais site ITS_home_projetos','','inherit','open','open','','curso-direitos-autorais-site-its_home_projetos-2','','','2015-07-01 17:47:43','2015-07-01 20:47:43','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Curso-Direitos-Autorais-site-ITS_home_projetos1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1580,3,'2015-07-01 17:56:50','2015-07-01 20:56:50','','Oficina Antivigilancia','','inherit','open','open','','oficina-antivigilancia','','','2015-07-01 17:56:50','2015-07-01 20:56:50','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Oficina-Antivigilancia.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1581,3,'2015-07-01 17:58:35','2015-07-01 20:58:35','','oficina antivigilancia home','','inherit','open','open','','oficina-antivigilancia-