:54','2016-02-15 15:28:54','','Daniel','','inherit','open','open','','daniel','','','2016-02-15 13:28:54','2016-02-15 15:28:54','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Daniel.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2187,3,'2016-02-15 13:28:56','2016-02-15 15:28:56','','florian','','inherit','open','open','','florian','','','2016-02-15 13:28:56','2016-02-15 15:28:56','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/florian.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2188,3,'2016-02-15 13:28:57','2016-02-15 15:28:57','','karima','','inherit','open','open','','karima','','','2016-02-15 13:28:57','2016-02-15 15:28:57','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/karima.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2199,3,'2016-02-15 18:05:55','2016-02-15 20:05:55','<!--:en--><font size=\"4\"><p align=\"middle\"><strong>Daniel Arnaudo</strong></p></font>\n<p align=\"middle\"><a href=\"https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Daniel.png\"><img src=\"https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Daniel.png\" alt=\"Daniel\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2186\" /></a></p>\n\nThe ITS fellowship is a great opportunity to work in one of the most interesting places in the world to study the intersection of technology and policy. As a student of the Marco Civil, I found the fellowship an incredibly interesting and engaging window into Brazil\'s Internet society. If you want to understand how Internet governance can work in a democratic system, one that is now becoming one of the major models for the world, come to Rio and learn at ITS. We had great conversations with experts, academics and practitioners from all sectors of government, business and civil society. Overall, an excellent experience, and a great view of the Sugarloaf right outside your office!\n\n<font size=\"4\"><p align=\"middle\"><strong>Florian Martin-Bariteau</strong></p></font>\n<p align=\"middle\"><a href=\"https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/florian.png\"><img src=\"https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/florian.png\" alt=\"florian\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2187\" /></a></p>\n\nThe Global Fellowship was an unrivalled experience to better understand global internet policy issues and discuss the future of law, society and technology.\n	\nITS is home of some of the highest respected Brazilian scholars in the field, and full of passionate and inspiring people working* for a better digital future. They shared their experience, ideas, questionings, and concerns with us but also their network within government, industry, and civil society. Meeting with telcos, Internet stakeholders, regulatory agencies, government policy makers, civil liberties advocates, etc. to discuss, and argue, about tech policy has been an extraordinary opportunity, not just to better understand technological and political Brazilian landscape, but also in our home countries.\n\nIf we have been brief on a lot of issues, we also had the chance to present our researches to fellows, ITS’ staff, but also to the Rio tech policy scene during the Varandas. This was really helpful!\n\nI think the diversity of backgrounds, geographical origins, and research fields of the Fellows helped to design a very inclusive and open thinking atmosphere. This was a terrific experience! And it also fostered new and upcoming projects between fellows, and between fellows and the ITS team.\n\n*Did I mention it was in Rio? And the office has a sea view. I will absolutely come back.\n\n\n<font size=\"4\"><p align=\"middle\"><strong>Payal Arora</strong></p></font>\n<p align=\"middle\"><a href=\"https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Payal-Arora1.png\"><img src=\"https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Payal-Arora1.png\" alt=\"Payal Arora\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2209\" /></a></p>\n\nI would 100% do this Fellowship again. ITS Rio provided an excellent climate and a powerful entry point into Brazilian policy and practice on Internet regulation by exposing us to a range of high level practitioners in the private and public sector. This, coupled with the fact that ITS itself is at the forefront of fascinating research and public outreach in this area makes this a rare fellowship of engagement. Of course, this experience is unforgettable due to the hospitality and warmth of the team and the bonding among the fellows from different fields and countries in this intense one month period in one of the most exciting cities in the world.\n\n<font size=\"4\"><p align=\"middle\"><strong>Roxana Radu</strong></p></font>\n<p align=\"middle\"><a href=\"https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Roxana-Radu.png\"><img src=\"https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Roxana-Radu.png\" alt=\"karima\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2188\" /></a></p>\n\n\nThere is no greater sense of immersion than to be in the midst of policy discussions as developments unfold. The fellowship program achieved exactly that - with a group of amazing people. From samba nights to formal meetings, the blending of local insights and global perspectives made the interactions very valuable. I recommend the program with high enthusiasm.\n\n<font size=\"4\"><p align=\"middle\"><strong>Smouk Karima</strong></p></font>\n<p align=\"middle\"><a href=\"https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/karima.png\"><img src=\"https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/karima.png\" alt=\"karima\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2188\" /></a></p>\n\nI have only one word to express my feeling about my experience: AMAZING.\n\nIt was an amazing experience, an amazing opportunity, you are amazing people, it was an amazing way to share knowledge, and everything was just amazing.\n\nThere is no doubt that I will spend the word about the next fellowship.<!--:-->','(English) ITS Fellows 2015 and what they said about their experience','','publish','closed','closed','','english-its-fellows-2015-and-what-they-said-about-their-experience','','','2016-02-15 18:05:55','2016-02-15 20:05:55','',0,'http://itsrio.org/?p=2199',0,'comunicados_ctp','',0),(2209,3,'2016-02-15 15:52:08','2016-02-15 17:52:08','','Payal Arora','','inherit','open','open','','payal-arora-2','','','2016-02-15 15:52:08','2016-02-15 17:52:08','',2199,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Payal-Arora1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2214,3,'2016-02-15 17:40:43','2016-02-15 19:40:43','','Roxana Radu','','inherit','open','open','','roxana-radu','','','2016-02-15 17:40:43','2016-02-15 19:40:43','',2199,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Roxana-Radu.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2217,1,'2016-02-16 18:22:18','2016-02-16 20:22:18','<!--:en--><strong>Applications closed</strong>\n\nThe Institute for Technology and Society (ITS Rio) invites researchers, graduate students as well as professionals working with technology policy, to apply to its Global Policy Fellowship Program and spend four weeks* in Brazil at ITS. Last year, we welcomed seven felllows from all over the world, who contributted immensely for the success of the Fellowship Program. \n\nSee the list of our fellows <a href=\"http://itsrio.org/en/sobre-o-its/fellows/\">here</a>, and what they have to say about their experiences <a href=\"http://itsrio.org/en/2016/02/15/english-its-fellows-2015-and-what-they-said-about-their-experience/\">here</a>.\n\nOur Global Fellows will have the opportunity to work with the team who created and developed the landmark “Marco Civil” legislation, a bill protecting fundamental rights, including privacy, net neutrality and freedom of expression, approved as law in Brazil in April 2014. Also, they will be free to choose one of the ITS five broad areas to work with, namely: \n\n<ul>\n<li>Law, democracy and technology (dealing with topics such civic engagement, online participation, and others);</li>\n\n<li>Access to technology, justice and human rights (dealing with topics such as connectivity, accesibility, digital divide and others);</li>\n\n<li>Internet regulation and Internet governance;</li>\n\n<li>Privacy and data protection (dealing with topics such as big data, anti-survailance, data protection and mass surveilance);</li>\n\n<li>Rethinking culture, media and education  (working with topics such as intelectual property, digital entrepreneurship, art & technology, online teaching, and others).</li>\n</ul>\n \nThe ITS Fellowship Program will offer the opportunity for those interested in internet and technology policy to deepen their knowledge about the Brazilian technology context. We have prepared an intensive 4-week* program for our fellows, which includes visits to the biggest technology national and international companies operating in Brazil, the Brazilian Internet Steering Committee (CGI.br) and visits to São Paulo and Brasília, including meetings with representatives of the Ministry of Justice, Ministry of Culture, and Congress members who are advocating for policies related to internet and technology. \n\n<strong>During their stay, selected fellows will be expected to:</strong>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Present an online seminar, which will be broadcasted to the whole world and organized in partnership with ITS. Suggested topics can include: broadband and access policy, content regulation, copyright and creativity, consumer privacy, open government, government surveillance, data security, data innovation, freedom of expression, democracy and technology and human rights;</li>\n\n<li>Publish at least one article or webpost about their experience as a fellow in Brazil;</li>\n\n<li>Collaborate with the ITS team and its projects; </li>\n\n<li>Portuguese skills are not required (but English is mandatory);</li>\n</ul>\n\n<strong>Who should apply?</strong>\n\nWe are looking for students, researchers, and professionals who are following the debates in the public policy field, and who want to spend part of their summer/winter in Brazil, learning about Internet policy. People from all backgrounds are encouraged to apply.\n\n<strong>For the selection processes, you must:</strong>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Fill the application form <a href=\"https://itsrio2.typeform.com/to/S6rm6J\">here</a>;</li>\n\n<li>Send us your complete academic and professional resume (english), including your Linkedin profile and other online references you want us to consider;</li>\n\n</ul>\n\nAll documents must be sent in one single e-mail message to <strong>manuela.curcio@itsrio.org</strong>, with the subject “<strong>[ITS] Global Fellows Application :: YOUR NAME</strong>”.\n\n\n<strong>Our Fellowship Package includes:</strong>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Intensive 4-week* program for the fellows;</li>\n<li>Air tickets to São Paulo and Brasília;</li>\n<li>Accommodation in São Paulo and Brasília during the days of our visit;</li>                    	\n<li>Shared office space at our headquarters for four weeks*;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<strong>Our Fellowship Package does not include:</strong>\n\n<ul>\n<li>International Travelling to and from Brazil;</li>\n<li>Accommodation for the four weeks* in Rio de Janeiro, where our program takes place;</li>\n<li>Other costs related to your stay in Brazil, besides those mentioned above.</li>\n<li>Necessary visa to entry the country.</li> \n</ul>\n\nOur team will provide tips and information about how to find accommodation in the city during that time.\n\n<strong>Relevant Dates:</strong>\n\nApplications deadline: <strong>April 11th, 2016</strong>;\nAnnouncement of fellows by e-mail: <strong>April 25th, 2016</strong>;\nFellowship Program will start: <strong>July 04th</strong>, and will finish in <strong>August 01st, 2016</strong>*;\n \n<em>* Fellows are expected to stay in Rio from 04/July/2016 to 01/Aug/2016. After this date, fellows can coordinate with ITS the possibility of staying for a longer term if they wish. Visa and costs for additional stays are to be provided by the fellows.</em> </font><!--:-->','(English) Apply Now: ITS Global Policy Fellowship Program - 2016','','publish','closed','closed','','english-its-global-policy-fellowship-program-2016','','','2016-02-16 18:22:18','2016-02-16 20:22:18','',0,'http://itsrio.org/?p=2217',0,'comunicados_ctp','',0),(2235,3,'2016-02-16 18:01:57','2016-02-16 20:01:57','','ITS Global Policy Fellowship Form','','inherit','open','open','','its-global-policy-fellowship-form','','','2016-02-16 18:01:57','2016-02-16 20:01:57','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/ITS-Global-Policy-Fellowship-Form.docx',0,'attachment','application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document',0),(2236,3,'2016-02-16 18:15:28','2016-02-16 20:15:28','','FBcover_fellowship_851x315-02','','inherit','open','open','','fbcover_fellowship_851x315-02','','','2016-02-16 18:15:28','2016-02-16 20:15:28','',2217,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/FBcover_fellowship_851x315-02.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2282,3,'2016-03-07 17:38:24','2016-03-07 20:38:24','','Consulta Pública - decreto de regulação2','','inherit','open','open','','consulta-publica-decreto-de-regulacao2','','','2016-03-07 17:38:24','2016-03-07 20:38:24','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Consulta-Pública-decreto-de-regulação2.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(2284,3,'2016-03-07 17:47:51','2016-03-07 20:47:51','','Consulta Pública - decreto de regulação5','','inherit','open','open','','consulta-publica-decreto-de-regulacao5','','','2016-03-07 17:47:51','2016-03-07 20:47:51','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Consulta-Pública-decreto-de-regulação5.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(2286,3,'2016-03-07 18:55:42','2016-03-07 21:55:42','','Consulta Viário SP','','inherit','open','open','','consulta-viario-sp','','','2016-03-07 18:55:42','2016-03-07 21:55:42','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Consulta-Viário-SP.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(2288,3,'2016-03-07 20:35:48','2016-03-07 23:35:48','','Big Data in the Global South Project','','inherit','open','open','','big-data-in-the-global-south-project','','','2016-03-07 20:35:48','2016-03-07 23:35:48','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Big-Data-in-the-Global-South-Project.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(2301,3,'2016-03-15 17:42:15','2016-03-15 20:42:15','','ITS_Relatorio_Big-Data_PT-BR_v2','','inherit','open','open','','its_relatorio_big-data_pt-br_v2','','','2016-03-15 17:42:15','2016-03-15 20:42:15','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/ITS_Relatorio_Big-Data_PT-BR_v2.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(2302,3,'2016-03-15 17:44:29','2016-03-15 20:44:29','','site - capa','','inherit','open','open','','site-capa','','','2016-03-15 17:44:29','2016-03-15 20:44:29','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/site-capa.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2303,3,'2016-03-15 17:46:39','2016-03-15 20:46:39','','site - miniatura','','inherit','open','open','','site-miniatura','','','2016-03-15 17:46:39','2016-03-15 20:46:39','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/site-miniatura.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2308,1,'2016-03-18 14:17:27','2016-03-18 17:17:27','<!--:pt--><em>Inscrições encerradas</em>\n\n\nO Instituto de Tecnologia e Sociedade do Rio convida estudantes e profissionais a se candidatarem para fazer parte do Grupo de Pesquisa ITS. Ele será coordenado pelo professor Sérgio Branco e outros membros do instituto, todos especialistas no assunto. \n\nO Grupo de Pesquisa terá por foco o tema <strong>privacidade na Internet</strong>. Os pesquisadores irão discutir temas como: privacidade como direito fundamental, privacidade e direitos humanos, privacidade e acesso à informação, privacidade e Marco Civil da Internet, direito ao esquecimento, iniciativas legislativas sobre proteção de dados pessoais, big data, sociedade do algoritmo, internet das coisas (IoT), privacidade e segurança pública, privacidade e a sociedade da vigilância, entre outros.\n\n<strong>- Qual o perfil do pesquisador? </strong>\nO grupo é dirigido para estudantes de graduação ou graduados em quaisquer áreas de conhecimento com interesse em discutir os temas relacionados neste edital. \n\n<strong>- Quais atividades serão oferecidas?</strong> \nDurante um ano, o grupo vai pesquisar questões relativas à privacidade na internet. Os encontros serão mensais, realizados exclusivamente <strong>ao vivo online</strong> e conduzidos em plataforma interativa utilizada pelo ITS Rio.\n\nA cada encontro será apresentado e debatido um tema específico, com condução de um professor do ITS Rio e participação dos integrantes do grupo de pesquisa. No período entre um encontro e outro, os temas continuarão a ser debatidos na internet. Os participantes deverão produzir artigos científicos a serem entregues ao final do ciclo do grupo de pesquisa. Os artigos poderão ser escritos em português ou inglês e deverão ser licenciados por meio de Licença Creative Commons (CC-BY-NC-SA) para possível impressão e divulgação nas redes nacionais e internacionais do ITS Rio. \n\n<strong>- Que tipo de certificado é oferecido?</strong>\nReceberá certificado quem participar em pelo menos 6 dos encontros online e entregar no prazo o artigo de conclusão. \n\nPara fins acadêmicos, será atribuído certificado de 60h de atividades complementares para os que cumprirem com os requisitos acima. \n\n<strong>- Qual o calendário do grupo de pesquisa?</strong>\nO grupo de pesquisa tem duração de um ano. \n\n- 8 de Abril 2016: primeiro encontro ao vivo online\n- 11 de Novembro 2016: último encontro ao vivo online\n- Janeiro 2017: entrega do artigo de pesquisa\n\nOs encontros acontecerão às sextas, uma vez por mês, das 10h30min às 12h, por meio da plataforma interativa do ITS.\n<em>Agenda provável dos encontros ao vivo online, sujeita a modificação:</em> \n\n1º Encontro - 08/04\n2º Encontro - 13/05\n3º Encontro - 10/06\n4º Encontro - 08/07\n5º Encontro - 12/08\n6º Encontro - 09/09\n7º Encontro - 14/10\n8º Encontro - 11/11\n\n\n<strong>Processo seletivo:</strong>\nInscrições encerradas\nO resultado será anunciado dia 04/04\nVagas: 10\n\n<strong>Professores: </strong>\n\nSérgio Branco\nDoutor em Direito Civil pela UERJ. Pós-graduado em cinema documentário pela FGV. Autor dos livros “Direitos Autorais na Internet e o Uso de Obras Alheias”, “O Domínio Público no Direito Autoral Brasileiro” e “O que é Creative Commons?”. Diretor do ITS.\n\nRonaldo Lemos\nDoutor pela USP, professor da graduação e da pós-graduação da UERJ. Pesquisador visitante do MIT Midia Lab. Diretor do projeto Creative Commons no Brasil e co-fundador do projeto Overmundo. Apresenta o programa Navegador, na Globonews. Diretor do ITS.\n\nCarlos Affonso Souza\nDoutor pela UERJ, professor da graduação e da pós-graduação da UERJ. Pesquisador Visitante do Information Society Project, da Faculdade de Direito da Universidade de Yale. Diretor do ITS.\n\nMario Viola\nAdvogado, Doutor em Direito e Master of Research pelo European University Institute, na Itália. Mestre em Direito Civil e Especialista em Direito do Consumidor pela UERJ e Especialista em Direito Privado pela UFF.<!--:-->','Lançamento do Grupo de Pesquisa ITS','','publish','closed','closed','','grupo-de-pesquisa-do-its-rio','','','2016-03-18 14:17:27','2016-03-18 17:17:27','',0,'http://itsrio.org/?p=2308',0,'comunicados_ctp','',0),(2332,3,'2016-03-21 14:50:13','2016-03-21 17:50:13','','pareceiria-fb','','inherit','open','open','','pareceiria-fb','','','2016-03-21 14:50:13','2016-03-21 17:50:13','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/pareceiria-fb.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2333,3,'2016-03-21 14:54:59','2016-03-21 17:54:59','<!--:pt--><em>Inscrições encerradas</em>\n\nO Instituto de Tecnologia e Sociedade do Rio de Janeiro (ITS Rio) convida suas ex-alunas e ex-alunos de cursos online a se candidatarem a uma vaga para participar de seu projeto sobre ensino online em colaboração com MobGeek e MIT Media Lab.\n\n<strong>Objetivo:</strong>\nFalamos muito do grande potencial do ensino online, sobretudo no que trata de permitir o acesso a uma educação de qualidade a todos e em particular aos países emergentes. Entretanto, o que se constata hoje, na maioria dos cursos online, é: abandono alto e pouco engajamento, sobretudo por parte das alunas e alunos que fazem cursos online pela primeira vez. Precisamos mudar esse cenário.\n\nEssa colaboração entre MobGeek, ITS Rio e MIT Media Lab tem por objetivo definir a melhor metodologia para promover interação e engajamento de qualidade em comunidades de ensino online. Vamos conectar as experiencias da Mobgeek e do ITS Rio na área de cursos online com as ferramentas de colaboração de ensino online e pesquisas do MIT MediaLab nessa mesma área. \n\n<strong>O que oferecemos?</strong>\nA pessoa que for selecionada participará do projeto para debater e avaliar novas metodologias de ensino online. Isso implica a participação do Alumni nas seguintes atividades ao longo do projeto:\n\n- Workshop de uma semana no MIT MediaLab \n- Workshop de uma semana no Rio de Janeiro \n- Reuniões mensais online com os colaboradores do projeto para discutir experiências e ferramentas de ensino online\n\n<strong>Como vamos fazer a seleção? </strong>\nPode se candidatar qualquer pessoa que já tenha feito um curso online oferecido pelo ITS Rio, tendo recebido certificado de conclusão com êxito e que agora faça parte da comunidade ITS Alumni. O ITS Rio fará uma pré-seleção dentre os inscritos e a seleção final será feita por uma comissão independente. \n\n<strong>Qual o calendário?</strong>\nDatas do projeto: Abril de 2016 → Agosto de 2017\nSemana de workshop no MIT MediaLab: 23/05/2016 → 27/05/2016 \nSemana de workshop no Rio de Janeiro: provavelmente setembro de 2016 (datas a definir)\n\n<strong>Questões administrativas?</strong>\nCom relação ao workshop a ser realizado no MIT Media Lab, em maio de 2016, os seguintes custos serão arcados pelo projeto:\n\n- Passagens aérea Rio de Janeiro - Boston - Rio de Janeiro\n- Hospedagem\n- Diárias  \n\n<strong>Processo seletivo:</strong>\nInscrições encerradas\nO resultado será anunciado dia 06/04\nVaga: 1<!--:-->','Edital para Alumni ITS - Comunidades de ensino online','','publish','closed','closed','','edital-para-alumni-its-comunidades-de-ensino-online-2','','','2016-03-21 14:54:59','2016-03-21 17:54:59','',0,'http://itsrio.org/?p=2333',0,'comunicados_ctp','',0),(2353,3,'2016-04-04 13:31:16','2016-04-04 16:31:16','','sd','','inherit','open','open','','sd','','','2016-04-04 13:31:16','2016-04-04 16:31:16','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/sd.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2355,3,'2016-04-04 13:40:11','2016-04-04 16:40:11','','sds','','inherit','open','open','','sds','','','2016-04-04 13:40:11','2016-04-04 16:40:11','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/sds.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2361,3,'2016-04-04 13:53:33','2016-04-04 16:53:33','','er','','inherit','open','open','','er','','','2016-04-04 13:53:33','2016-04-04 16:53:33','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/er.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2364,3,'2016-04-04 14:05:10','2016-04-04 17:05:10','','qq','','inherit','open','open','','qq','','','2016-04-04 14:05:10','2016-04-04 17:05:10','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/qq.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2365,3,'2016-04-04 14:06:28','2016-04-04 17:06:28','','weqwe','','inherit','open','open','','weqwe','','','2016-04-04 14:06:28','2016-04-04 17:06:28','',0,'https://its.hacklab.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/weqwe.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2382,1,'2016-04-04 23:59:03','2016-04-05 02:59:03','<!--:pt-->O 1º Gr